DESC.L-2: Configuration of the CAN (Controller Area Networks) module.
This is the multiple configuration set container for CAN Driver.
This parameter specifies the number of Receive Buffer supported for CANFD hardware in classical CAN mode (RS-CANFD).
This parameter specifies the number of Receive FIFO supported for CANFD hardware in classical CAN mode (RS-CANFD).

This parameter specifies number of Receive Rules supported for each CAN channel. Format of this parameter's literal is as follows: "CANCanControllerInstance_TO_CanControllerInstance_NumberOfReceiveRulesupported".

P.L-1: CAN0_TO_2_128: Each CAN Channel from 0 to 2 supports 128 Receive Rules.

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies the total real amount of receive buffer, receive FIFO buffer and RX/TX FIFO buffer, namely 128 for a 3-channel RS-CANFD. CanControllerMaxSharedBuffer = total receive buffers + total receive FIFO buffers + total Transmit/receive FIFO buffers.

This parameter specifies number of Transmit Buffers supported for each CAN channel. Format of this parameter's literal is as follows: "CANCanControllerInstance_TO_CanControllerInstance_TransmitBufferSupported".

P.L-1: CAN0_TO_2_16: Each CAN Channel from 0 to 2 supports 16 Transmit Buffers.

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies number of Transmit Queue supported for each CAN channel. Format of this parameter's literal is as follows: "CANCanControllerInstance_TO_CanControllerInstance_NumberOfTransmitQueuesupported".

P.L-1: CAN0_TO_2_1: Each CAN Channel from 0 to 2 supports 1 Transmit Queue.

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies number of Tx/Rx FIFO supported for each CAN channel. Format of this parameter's literal is as follows: "CANCanControllerInstance_TO_CanControllerInstance_NumberOfTx/RxFIFOSupported".

P.L-1: CAN0_TO_2_3: Each CAN Channel from 0 to 2 supports 3 Tx/Rx FIFO.

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies the total memory of receive buffer in FD mode, receive FIFO buffer and RX/TX FIFO buffer, namely 3584 for a 8-channel RS-CAN. CanCtlrMaxSharedBufferMemory =(( Number of receive buffers * (12 + payload storage size)) + total of (number of depth * (12 +payload storage size)) of receive FIFO buffers + total of (number of depth * (12 + payload storage size)) of transmit/receive FIFO buffers ) should be less than 3584 bytes. CAN0_TO_3584_BYTES: Maximum supported shared buffer for CAN module 0(RSCAN0).

This parameter specifies the total real amount of receive buffer, receive FIFO buffer and RX/TX FIFO buffer, namely 128 for a 3-channel RS-CANFD. CanCtlrMaxSharedBufferModule = total receive buffers + total receive FIFO buffers + total Transmit/receive FIFO buffers. CAN0_TO_2_128: Maximum supported shared buffer for CAN module 0(RSCAN0).
This parameter specifies the maximum number of CAN Module supported(RS-CANFDn).
This container contains the configuration parameters of the CAN controller(s).
Enables / disables API Can_MainFunction_BusOff for handling Busoff events in polling mode.

P.L-1: INTERRUPT: Interrupt Mode of operation. POLLING: Polling Mode of operation.

DESC.L-2: Define whether the CAN Controller is used in the configuration.

P.L-1: true: CAN Controller is used in the configuration. false: CAN Controller is not used in the configuration.

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies the CAN controller base address. This parameter is not used for implementation.
This parameter provides the controller ID which is unique in a given CAN Driver. The value for this parameter starts with 0 and continues without any gaps.
This parameter provides selection of hardware CAN controller.

P.L-1: CANFD00: CAN Controller 0 is selected. CANFD01: CAN Controller 1 is selected. CANFD02: CAN Controller 2 is selected.

DESC.L-2: Defines buffer merge mode is used for CAN FD of respective controller. This parameter should be configured only when CanFdSupport parameter configured as true.

P.L-1: true: CAN FD Buffer merge mode is enabled. false: CAN FD Buffer merge mode is disabled.

DESC.L-2: Enables / disables API Can_MainFunction_Read for handling PDU Reception events in polling mode.

P.L-1: INTERRUPT: Interrupt Mode of operation. POLLING: Polling Mode of operation.

DESC.L-2: Enables / disables API Can_MainFunction_Write for handling PDU Transmission events in polling mode.

P.L-1: INTERRUPT: Interrupt Mode of operation. POLLING: Polling Mode of operation.

DESC.L-2: Adds / removes the service Can_CheckWakeup() from the code. This parameters is not used for implementation since CAN HW doesn't support wakeup detection over CAN bus.
Enables / disables API Can_MainFunction_Wakeup for handling Wakeup events in polling mode. This parameters is not used for implementation since CAN HW doesn't support wakeup detection over CAN bus.
Specify whether CAN driver wakeup shall be supported. This parameters is not used for implementation since CAN HW doesn't support wakeup detection over CAN bus.
Reference to baudrate configuration container configured for the Can Controller.

P.L-1: Implementation Type: reference to CanControllerBaudrateConfig.

DESC.L-2: Reference to the CPU clock configuration, which is set in the MCU driver configuration. This parameter is not used for implementation since CanControllerCANFDclkClock parameter in CanGlobalConfiguration container is used instead.

P.L-1: Implementation Type: reference to McuClockReferencePoint.

DESC.L-2: This parameter contains a reference to the Wakeup Source for this controller as defined in the ECU State Manager. This parameters is not used for implementation since CAN HW doesn't support wakeup detection over CAN bus.
This container contains bit timing related configuration parameters of the CAN controller(s).
This parameter specifies the baud rate of the Controller in kbps.

P.L-1: BaudRate = fCAN/((BRP + 1) * Tq count per bit) Where fCAN:Frequency of CAN clock, Tq count per bit is Time quantum calculated as Tq count per bit = (CanControllerTSeg1 + CanControllerSeg2 + SS), BRP: Baud rate prescaler division value. Note: [TSEG1 > TSEG2 >= SJW], SS: synchronization segment value is always 1 tq.

DESC.L-2: Uniquely identifies a specific baud rate configuration. This ID is used by SetBaudrate API.
This parameter specifies propagation delay in time quantas. This parameter is not used for the implementation since CanControllerTSeg1 parameter is used instead.
This parameter specifies phase segment 1 in time quantas. This parameter is not used for the implementation since CanControllerTSeg1 parameter is used instead.

This parameter specifies Tq value for the length of phase segment 2 (PHASE_SEG2). This parameter represents the TSEG2[2:0] bit in RSCFDnCmCFG Channel Configuration Register and the NTSEG2[4:0] bit in RSCFDnCFDCmNCFG Channel Normal Bit Rate Configuration Register.

This parameter specifies the SJW (Synchronization Jump Width) value of the controller in time quantas. This parameter represents the SJW[1:0] bit in RSCFDnCmCFG Channel Configuration Register and the NSJW[4:0] bit in RSCFDnCFDCmNCFG Channel Normal Bit Rate Configuration Register.

This parameter specifies the total length of the propagation segment (PROP_SEG) and phase segment 1 (PHASE_SEG1). This parameter represents the TSEG1[3:0] bit in RSCFDnCmCFG Channel Configuration Register and the NTSEG1[6:0] bit in RSCFDnCFDCmNCFG Channel Normal Bit Rate Configuration Register.

This optional container contains bit timing related configuration parameters of the CAN controller(s) for payload and CRC of a CAN FD frame. If this container exists the controller supports CAN FD frames.
Specifies the data segment baud rate of the controller in kbps.

P.L-1: DataBaudRate = fCAN/((DBRP + 1) * Tq count per bit) Where fCAN:Frequency of CAN clock, Tq count per bit is Time quantum calculated as Tq count per bit = (CanControllerTSeg1 + CanControllerSeg2 + SS), DBRP: Data Bit Rate Prescaler Division Ratio. Note: [TSEG1 > TSEG2 >= SJW], SS: synchronization segment value is always 1 tq.

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies propagation delay in time quantas. This parameter is not used for the implementation since CanControllerTSeg1 parameter is used instead.
This parameter specifies phase segment 1 in time quantas. This parameter is not used for the implementation since CanControllerTSeg1 parameter is used instead.
This parameter specifies Tq value for the length of phase segment 2 (PHASE_SEG2). This parameter represents the DTSEG2[2:0] bit in RSCFDnCFDCmDCFG Channel Configuration Register.
This parameter specifies the SJW (Synchronization Jump Width) value of the controller in time quantas. This parameter represents the DSJW[1:0] bit in RSCFDnCFDCmDCFG Channel Configuration Register.

This parameter specifies the total length of the propagation segment (PROP_SEG) and phase segment 1 (PHASE_SEG1). This parameter represents the DTSEG1[3:0] bit in RSCFDnCmDCFG Channel Configuration Register.
Specifies the Transceiver Delay Compensation Offset in ns. If not specified Transceiver Delay Compensation is disabled.

P.L-1: This parameter should be configured when transmission carry out(in FD mode only) with high Data BaudRate(i.e above 2.5 Mbps) or HW Transceiver has high delay time(Td). Parameter CanControllerTrcvDelayCompensationOffset is used to compensate the delay time when CAN Controller(Transmitter) monitoring its transmission on CAN bus. This parameter represents bit TDCO[6:0], TDCE, TDCOC in register RSCFDnCFDCmFDCFG. Transmit delay correction mechanism: SSP = Td + SSP Offset Where: SSP: Timing of Second Sampling Point. Td: Transceiver Delay( CAN HW support measure this delay). SSP Offset: Sampling point offset is the value of CanControllerTrcvDelayCompensationOffset and it must be the sum of SS(default value = 1Tq) and TSEG1. CanControllerTrcvDelayCompensationOffset(ns) = (CanControllerTSeg1 + 1)(quantum) * Time of an Tq(ns/quantum). The RS-CANFD module corrects the delay of a maximum of 3CANm bit time - 2Tq (the CANm bit time and Tq are the values of data bit rate).

DESC.L-2: Specifies if the bit rate switching shall be used for transmissions. If FALSE: CAN FD frames shall be sent without bit rate switching.
This container contains the configuration (parameters) of the CAN Filter Mask(s). This container and its parameters are not used for implementation since "CanReceiveRule" container is used instead.

This parameter describes mask for hardware-based filtering of CAN identifiers. The CAN identifiers of incoming messages are masked with the appropriate CanFilterMaskValue. Bits holding a 0 mean don't care, i.e. do not compare the message's identifier in the respective bit position. This parameter is not used for implementation since "CanReceiveIdMaskValue" parameter is used for instead.

P.L-1: The mask shall be build by filling with leading 0. In case of CanIdType EXTENDED or MIXED, a 29 bit mask shall be build. In case of CanIdType STANDARD a 11 bit mask shall be build.

DESC.L-2: This container is only included and valid if TTCAN SWS is used and TTCAN is enabled. This container is not used for implementation.

P.L-1: This container contains the configuration parameters of the TTCAN controller(s) (which are needed in addition to the configuration parameters of the CAN controller(s)). CanTTController is only included, if the controller supports TTCAN.

DESC.L-2: Defines the maximum time period (unit is 256 times NTU) after which the application has to serve the watchdog. This parameter is not used for implementation.
Defines the value for cycle_count_max. This parameter is not used for implementation.

P.L-1: Allowed values: 0x00: 1 basic cycle 0x01: 2 basic cycles 0x03: 4 basic cycles 0x07: 8 basic cycles 0x0F: 16 basic cycles 0x1F: 32 basic cycles 0x3F: 64 basic cycles

DESC.L-2: Number of expected_tx_trigger. This parameter is not used for implementation.
Enables/disables the external clock synchronization. This parameter is not used for implementation.

P.L-1: true: External clock synchronization enabled. false: External clock synchronization disabled. This parameter shall only be configurable if parameter CanTTControllerLevel2 equals true.

DESC.L-2: Enables/disables the global time filtering. This parameter is not used for implementation.

P.L-1: true: Global time filtering enabled. false: Global time filtering disabled. This parameter shall only be configurable if parameter CanTTControllerLevel2 equals true.

DESC.L-2: Defines the initial value for ref trigger offset. This parameter is not used for implementation.
Enables/disables the respective interrupts. This parameter is not used for implementation.

P.L-1:
Bit Position set to 1: Enable respective interrupt. Bit Position set to 0: Disable respective interrupt.
Bit Position / Interrupt Source: 10: Application Watchdog. 9: Watch Trigger reached. 8: Initialization Watch Trigger reached. 7: Change of Error Level. 6: Tx Overflow. 5: Tx Underflow. 4: Global Time Error. 3: Gap. 2: Start of Cycle. 1: Time Discontinuity. 0: Master State Change.
Bit position "1: Time Discontinuity" and "4: Global Time Error" shall only be configurable if parameter CanTTControllerLevel2 equals TRUE.

DESC.L-2: Defines whether Level 2 or Level 1 is used. This parameter is not used for implementation.

P.L-1: true: Level 2. false: Level 1. If this parameter is set to false then all parameters with dependency to CanTTControllerLevel2 need not be configured.

DESC.L-2: Defines the config value for NTU (network time unit). This parameter is not used for implementation.

P.L-1: Value given in microseconds. Together with the local oscillator period, the TUR (time unit ratio) can be derived from the NTU. This parameter shall only be configurable if parameter CanTTControllerLevel2 equals true.

DESC.L-2: Defines the operation mode. This parameter is not used for implementation.
Defines the maximum synchronization deviation. This parameter is not used for implementation.

P.L-1: Given as a percentage value of the NTU (network time unit). This parameter shall only be configurable if parameter CanTTControllerLevel2 equals true.

DESC.L-2: Enables/disables the TUR restore. This parameter is not used for implementation.

P.L-1: Note that the value configured for TUR can be derived from the value configured for NTU and the local oscillator period. true: TUR restore enabled. false: TUR restore disabled. This parameter shall only be configurable if parameter CanTTControllerLevel2 equals true.

DESC.L-2: Defines whether the controller acts as a potential time master. This parameter is not used for implementation.

P.L-1: true: Potential time master. false: Time slave.

DESC.L-2: Defines the time master priority. This parameter is not used for implementation.
Length of the tx enable window given in CAN bit times. This parameter is not used for implementation.

P.L-1: Definition parameter "CanTTControllerTxEnableWindowlength" is used such that: Length of enable window = CanTTControllerTxEnableWindowLength + 1

DESC.L-2: watch trigger time mark after a gap. This parameter is not used for implementation.
watch trigger time mark. This parameter is not used for implementation.
Enables / disables API Can_MainFunction_BusOff() for handling busoff events in polling mode. This parameter is not used for implementation.
This container contains the configuration (parameters) of CAN Hardware Objects.

Specifies the value which is used to pad unspecified data in CAN FD frames > 8 bytes for transmission. This is necessary due to the discrete possible values of the DLC if > 8 bytes. If the length of a PDU which was requested to be sent does not match the allowed DLC values, the remaining bytes up to the next possible value shall be padded with this value.
This parameter specifies the type (Full-CAN or Basic-CAN) of a Hardware Object.

P.L-1: FULL: Only one L-PDU (identifier) is handled by the Hardware Object. BASIC: Several L-PDUs are handled by the Hardware Object.

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies the number of hardware objects used to implement one HOH. In case of a HRH this parameter defines the number of elements in the hardware FIFO or the number of shadow buffers, in case of a HTH it defines the number of hardware objects used for multiplexed transmission or for a hardware FIFO used by a FullCAN HTH. This parameter is not used for implementation.

P.L-1: CAN driver provides hardware Multiplexed Transmission mechanism by configured TRANSMIT CanHardwareObject in TRANSMIT_RECEIVE_FIFO_MODE or TRANSMIT_QUEUE_MODE, which send L-PDUs in order of L-PDU priority to avoid transmit priority inversion.

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies whether the CanIdValue is of type STANDARD or EXTENDED identifier. This parameter is not used for implementation. - HTH object is configured by the upper layer. - HRH object CanIDType is configure in the parameter CanReceiveIdType in CanReceiveRule container.

P.L-1: ImplementationType: Can_IdType. EXTENDED: All the CANIDs are of type EXTENDED only (29 bit). STANDARD: All the CANIDs are of type STANDARD only (11 bit). STANDARD_FD :CAN FD frame with Standard CAN ID (11 bit). EXTENDED_FD :CAN FD frame with Extended CAN ID (29 bit). MIXED: The type of CANIDs can be both Standard or Extended.

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies the CanId value for object. This parameter is not used for implementation. - HTH object is configured by the upper layer. - HRH object is configured in the parameter CanReceiveIdValue in CanReceiveRule container.
This parameter specifies the Memory Mode (BUFFER/RECEIVE_FIFO/TRANSMIT_RECEIVE_FIFO/TRANSMIT_QUEUE/BUFFER_MERGE_MODE) of the Hardware Object.

P.L-1: BUFFER_MODE: Hardware Object is considered as normal memory buffer (RECEIVE or TRANSMIT CanObjectType). RECEIVE_FIFO_MODE: Hardware Object is considered as RECEIVE FIFO (RECEIVE CanObjectType). TRANSMIT_RECEIVE_FIFO_MODE: Hardware Object is considered as TRANSMIT/RECEIVE FIFO (all CanObjectType). TRANSMIT_QUEUE_MODE: Hardware Object is considered as TRANSMIT QUEUE (TRANSMIT CanObjectType). BUFFER_MERGE_MODE: Hardware Object is considered as TRANSMIT BUFFER MERGE MODE (TRANSMIT CanObjectType).

DESC.L-2: This parameter holds the handle ID of HRH or HTH. The value of this parameter is unique in a given CAN Driver, and it should start with 0 and continue without any gaps.

P.L-1: The HRH and HTH Ids are defined under two different name-spaces. Example: HRH0-0, HRH1-1, HTH0-2, HTH1-3.

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies whether the Hardware Object is used as Transmit or Receive object.

P.L-1: RECEIVE: Receive HOH. TRANSMIT: Transmit HOH. GATEWAY: Gateway Mode

DESC.L-2: This parameter is used to set the data length of the message to be transmitted from the transmit buffer. This parameter is applicable only when the CanObjectType is configured as TRANSMIT or GATEWAY mode. If device do not support CAN FD mode range of CanTransmitDataLength can be vary from 0 to 8 only.
This parameter defines if or if not Can supports the trigger-transmit API for this handle.

P.L-1: If this parameter is set to true the trigger-transmit API shall be supported. Otherwise the API is not supported.

DESC.L-2: Reference to CAN Controller to which the HTH is associated. This parameter is applicable only for HTH object (if CanObjectType is configured as TRANSMIT). For RECEIVE object, the parameter CanReceiveRuleControllerRef in CanReceiveRule container which refers to this Hardware Object is used instead.

P.L-1: Implementation Type: reference to CanController.

DESC.L-2: Reference to CAN Controller to which the HOH is associated.

P.L-1: Implementation Type: reference to CanMainFunctionRWPeriods.

DESC.L-2: This container is only valid for HRHs and contains the configuration (parameters) of one hardware filter. This container and its parameters are not used for implementation.

P.L-1: N/A

DESC.L-2: Specifies (together with the filter mask) the identifiers range that passes the hardware filter. This parameter is not used for implementation.

P.L-1: N/A

DESC.L-2: Describes a mask for hardware-based filtering of CAN identifiers. The CAN identifiers of incoming messages are masked with the appropriate CanFilterMaskValue. Bits holding a 0 mean don't care, i.e. do not compare the message's identifier in the respective bit position. The mask shall be build by filling with leading 0. In case of CanIdType EXTENDED or MIXED a 29 bit mask shall be build. In case of CanIdType STANDARD a 11 bit mask shall be build. This parameter is not used for implementation.

P.L-1: N/A

DESC.L-2: This container contains the configuration (parameters) of RECEIVE FIFO. CanReceiveFIFOConfiguration should be included, if the CanMemoryMode is configured as RECEIVE_FIFO_MODE in CanHardwareObject container.

This parameter specifies number of messages that can be stored in a single receive FIFO buffer. This parameter represents the RFDC[2:0] bits in RSCFDnRFCCx Receive FIFO Buffer Configuration and Control Register.

P.L-1: BUFFER_4: 4 messages in receive FIFO. BUFFER_8: 8 messages in receive FIFO. BUFFER_16: 16 messages in receive FIFO. BUFFER_32: 32 messages in receive FIFO. BUFFER_48: 48 messages in receive FIFO. BUFFER_64: 64 messages in receive FIFO. BUFFER_128: 128 messages in receive FIFO.

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies the Enable/Disable the RECEIVE FIFO interrupt. This parameter represents the RFIE bit in RSCFDnRFCCx Receive FIFO Buffer Configuration and Control Register.

P.L-1: true: Receive FIFO interrupt is enabled. false: Receive FIFO interrupt is disabled.

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies the RECEIVE FIFO interrupt source. This parameter should be configured, when the parameter CanReceiveFIFOInterruptEnable is configured as TRUE. This parameter represents the RFIM bit in RSCFDnRFCCx Receive FIFO Buffer Configuration and Control Register.

P.L-1: true: An interrupt occurs each time a message has been received. false: An interrupt occurs at a specified time selected by the CanReceiveFIFOInterruptTimeSel parameter.

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies the timing of generating a receive FIFO interrupt request. This parameter should be configured, when the parameters CanReceiveFIFOInterruptSrcSel is configured as FALSE and CanReceiveFIFOInterruptEnable are configured as TRUE. This parameter represents the RFIGCV[2:0] bits in RSCFDnRFCCx Receive FIFO Buffer Configuration and Control Register.

P.L-1: FIFO_1_BY_8: When FIFO is 1/8 full. FIFO_2_BY_8: When FIFO is 2/8 full. FIFO_3_BY_8: When FIFO is 3/8 full. FIFO_4_BY_8: When FIFO is 4/8 full. FIFO_5_BY_8: When FIFO is 5/8 full. FIFO_6_BY_8: When FIFO is 6/8 full. FIFO_7_BY_8: When FIFO is 7/8 full. FIFO_8_BY_8: When FIFO is full.

DESC.L-2: This container contains the configuration (parameters) of Transmit Queue. CanTransmitQueueConfiguration should be included, if the CanMemoryMode is configured as QUEUE_MODE in CanHardwareObject container.

This parameter is used to set the number of transmit buffers to be allocated to the transmit queue. This parameter represents the TXQDC[3:0] bits in RSCFDnTXQCCm Transmit Queue Configuration and Control Register.
This parameter specifies the Enable/Disable the TRANSMIT Queue interrupt. This parameter represents the TXQIE bit in RSCFDnTXQCCm Transmit Queue Configuration and Control Register.

P.L-1: true: TRANSMIT Queue interrupt is enabled. false: TRANSMIT Queue interrupt is disabled.

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies the transmit queue interrupt source. This parameter should be configured, when the parameter CanTransmitQueueInterruptSource is configured as TRUE. This parameter represents the TXQIM bit in RSCFDnTXQCCm Transmit Queue Configuration and Control Register.

P.L-1: true: A transmit queue interrupt request is generated each time a message has been transmitted. false: When the buffer becomes empty upon completion of message transmission, a transmit queue interrupt request is generated.

DESC.L-2: This container is only included and valid if TTCAN SWS is used and TTCAN is enabled. This container and its parameters are not used for implementation.

P.L-1: This container contains the configuration (parameters) of TTCAN triggers for Hardware Objects, which are additional to the configuration (parameters) of CAN Hardware Objects. CanTTHardwareObjectTrigger is only included, if the controller supports TTCAN.

DESC.L-2: This parameter defines the cycle_offset. This parameter is not used for implementation.

P.L-1: CanTTHardwareObjectBaseCycle must be not greater than cycle_count_max.

DESC.L-2: This parameter defines the repeat_factor. This parameter is not used for implementation.

P.L-1: CanTTHardwareObjectCycleRepetition shall be a power of two (2), greater than cycle_offset but not greater than cycle_count_max + 1.

DESC.L-2: This parameter defines the point in time, when the trigger will be activated. This parameter is not used for implementation.

P.L-1: Value is given in cycle time.

DESC.L-2: This parameter defines sequential number which allows separation of different TTCAN triggers configured for one and the same Hardware Object. This parameter is not used for implementation.
This parameter defines the type of the trigger associated with the Hardware Object. This parameter depends on plain CAN parameter CAN_OBJECT_TYPE. This parameter is not used for implementation.

P.L-1: If CAN_OBJECT_TYPE equals RECEIVE then this parameter is fixed to CAN_TT_RX_TRIGGER. If CAN_OBJECT_TYPE equals TRANSMIT than one of the following literals is configurable: - CAN_TT_TX_REF_TRIGGER, - CAN_TT_TX_REF_TRIGGER_GAP, - CAN_TT_TX_TRIGGER_MERGED, - CAN_TT_TX_TRIGGER_SINGLE, - CAN_TT_TX_TRIGGER_EXCLUSIVE.

DESC.L-2: This container contains the configuration (parameters) of Transmit/Receive FIFO. CanTxRxFIFOConfiguration should be included, if the CanMemoryMode is configured as TRANSMIT_RECEIVE_FIFO_MODE in CanHardwareObject container.

This parameter specifies number of messages that can be transmitted or received in a single TRANSMIT/RECEIVE FIFO. This parameter represents the CFDC[2:0] bits in RSCFDnCFCCk Transmit/Receive FIFO Buffer Configuration and Control Register.

P.L-1: BUFFER_4: 4 messages in TRANSMIT/RECEIVE FIFO. BUFFER_8: 8 messages in TRANSMIT/RECEIVE FIFO. BUFFER_16: 16 messages in TRANSMIT/RECEIVE FIFO. BUFFER_32: 32 messages in TRANSMIT/RECEIVE FIFO. BUFFER_48: 48 messages in TRANSMIT/RECEIVE FIFO. BUFFER_64: 64 messages in TRANSMIT/RECEIVE FIFO. BUFFER_128: 128 messages in TRANSMIT/RECEIVE FIFO.

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies the Enable/Disable the TRANSMIT/RECEIVE FIFO interrupt. This parameter represents the CFRXIE or CFTXIE bit in RSCFDnCFCCk Transmit/Receive FIFO Buffer Configuration and Control Register.

P.L-1: true: If object is in receive mode, RECEIVE FIFO interrupt is enabled. If the object is in transmit mode, TRANSMIT FIFO interrupt is enabled. false: If object is in receive mode, RECEIVE FIFO interrupt is disabled. If the object is in transmit mode, TRANSMIT FIFO interrupt is disabled.

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies the TRANSMIT/RECEIVE FIFO interrupt source. This parameter should be configured, when the parameter CanTxRxFIFOInterruptEnable is configured as TRUE. This parameter represents the CFIM bit in RSCFDnCFCCk Transmit/Receive FIFO Buffer Configuration and Control Register.

P.L-1: true: A transmit/receive FIFO interrupt request is generated each time a message has been transmitted/received. false: An interrupt occurs at a specified time selected by the CanTxRxFIFOInterruptTimeSel parameter.

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies the timing of generating a TRANSMIT/RECEIVE FIFO interrupt request. This parameter should be configured, when the parameters CanTxRxFIFOInterruptEnable is configured as TRUE and CanTxRxFIFOInterruptSourceSelect are configured as FALSE. This parameter represents the CFIGCV[2:0] bits in RSCFDnCFCCk Transmit/Receive FIFO Buffer Configuration and Control Register.

P.L-1: FIFO_1_BY_8: When FIFO is 1/8 full. FIFO_2_BY_8: When FIFO is 2/8 full. FIFO_3_BY_8: When FIFO is 3/8 full. FIFO_4_BY_8: When FIFO is 4/8 full. FIFO_5_BY_8: When FIFO is 5/8 full. FIFO_6_BY_8: When FIFO is 6/8 full. FIFO_7_BY_8: When FIFO is 7/8 full. FIFO_8_BY_8: When FIFO is full.

DESC.L-2: This parameter is used to set a message transmission interval when transmitting messages continuously from a transmit/receive FIFO buffer. This parameter should be configured, if the CanObjectType is configured as transmit mode or gateway mode in CanHardwareObject container.

P.L-1: This parameter represents the CFITT[7:0] bits in RSCFDnCFCCk Transmit/Receive FIFO Buffer Configuration and Control Register. Interval time (s) = 2/pclk * CanIntervalTimerPrescalerSet(set ITRCP[15:0] value) * CanTxRxFIFOTransmissionInterval(set CFITT[7:0] value)

DESC.L-2: This container contains the configuration (parameters) of receive rules for Acceptance and DLC Filter processing. For each of the RECEIVE Hardware Object, CanReceiveRule container is mandatory. RSCFDnGAFLID, RSCFDnGAFLM, RSCFDnGAFLP0 and RSCFDnGAFLP1 registers of each HRH are configurable by this container.

This parameter describes minimum data length necessary for receiving messages for DLC-Filtering process. This parameter represents the GAFLDLC bits in RSCFDnGAFLP0 register for each Receive Rule Register.

P.L-1: If the data length of incoming message that is being filtered is equal to or larger than the value set by the CanDataLengthCheckValue, the message passes the DLC check.

DESC.L-2: This parameter describes CanId mask for hardware-based filtering of CAN identifiers. The CAN identifiers of incoming messages are masked with the appropriate CanReceiveIdMaskValue. Bits holding "1" mean don't care, i.e. do not compare the message's identifier in the respective bit position. This parameter represents the GAFLIDM bits in RSCFDnGAFLM for each Receive Rule Mask Register.

P.L-1: The mask shall be built by filling with leading 1. In case of EXTENDED CanReceiveIdType, a 29 bit mask shall be built. In case of STANDARD CanReceiveIdType, a 11 bit mask shall be built.

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies whether the CanReceiveIdValue is of type STANDARD or EXTENDED identifier. This parameter represents the GAFLIDE bit in RSCFDnGAFLID for each Receive Rule ID Register.

P.L-1: EXTENDED: All the CanReceiveIdValue are of type EXTENDED only (29 bit). STANDARD: All the CanReceiveIdValue are of type STANDARD only (11 bit). STANDARD_FD :CAN FD frame with Standard CAN ID (11 bit). EXTENDED_FD :CAN FD frame with Extended CAN ID (29 bit).

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies (together with the CanReceiveIdMaskValue) the CanId range that passes the hardware filter. This parameter represents the GAFLID bits in RSCFDnGAFLID for each Receive RuleID Register.
This parameter describes label information to be stored in the receive history buffer. This parameter represents the GAFLPTR bits in RSCFDnGAFLP0 register for each Receive Rule.

This parameter specifies the Receive Rule Target Message Select. This parameter represents the GAFLLB bit in RSCFDnGAFLID for each Receive Rule ID Register. This parameter should be configured as true, only when the parameter CanMirrorFunctionSupport is configured as true in CanGlobalConfiguration container.

P.L-1: true: When the mirror function is used, data processing using the receive rule is performed when the CAN node is receiving its own transmitted messages. false: Data processing using the receive rule is performed when receiving messages transmitted from another CAN node.

DESC.L-2: This parameter provides the Receive Rule ID which is unique in a RS-CANFD. The value for this parameter starts with 0 and continues without any gaps.
Reference to the CAN Controller Object.

P.L-1: Reference to the Can Controller, each of the RECEIVE Rule should assigned to any one of the CAN channel. Maximum Receive Rule for each channel depends upon the parameter CanControllerMaxReceiveRule. Implementation Type: reference to CanController.

DESC.L-2: Reference to the Receive (HRH) Object.

P.L-1: For each of the RECEIVE object, CanReceiveRule is mandatory. One CanHardwareObject can be mapped to multiple CanReceiveRule. Implementation Type: reference to CanHardwareObject.

DESC.L-2: This container contains the parameters for configuring pretended networking.
This container contains the configuration parameters of the ICOM Configuration.
This parameter identifies the ID of the ICOM configuration. The value of this parameter is unique in a given CAN Driver, and it should start with 1 and continue without any gaps.
This parameter defines that the MCU shall wake if the bus off is detected or not.

P.L-1: true: MCU shall wake if the bus off is detected. false: MCU shall not wake if the bus off is detected.

DESC.L-2: This container contains the configuration parameters of the wakeup causes to leave the power saving mode.

This container contains the configuration parameters for the wakeup causes for matching received messages. It has to be configured as often as received messages are defined as wakeup cause. For all CanIcomRxMessage instances the Message IDs which are defined in CanIcomMessageId and in CanIcomRxMessageIdMask shall not overlap.
This parameter defines that the MCU shall wake if the message with the ID is received n times on the communication channel.

This parameter defines the message ID the wakeup causes of this CanIcomRxMessage are configured for. In addition a mask (CanIcomMessageIdMask) can be defined, in that case it is possible to define a range of rx messages, which can create a wakeup condition.

Describes a mask for filtering of CAN identifiers. The CAN identifiers of incoming messages are masked with this CanIcomMessageIdMask. If the masked identifier matches the masked value of CanIcomMessageId, it can create a wakeup condition for this CanIcomRxMessage. Bits holding a 0 mean don't care, i.e. do not compare the message's identifier in the respective bit position. The mask shall be build by filling with leading 0. When the mask is not configured, only message have the same ID with CanIcomMessageId creates a wakeup condition. CanIcomMessageIdMask and CanIcomRxMessageSignalConfig shall not be defined together.
This parameter defines container index for CanIcomRxMessage. The value of this parameter is unique in a given CAN Icom configuration, and it should start with 0 and continue without any gaps.
This parameter defines that the MCU shall wake if the message with the ID is not received for a specific time in s on the communication channel.
This parameter defines that the MCU shall wake if a payload error occurs.

P.L-1: true: MCU shall wake if a payload error occurs. false: MCU shall not wake if a payload error occurs.

DESC.L-2: This parameter defines Payload Length Value for CanIcomRxMessage. This parameter should be configured when parameter CanIcomPayloadLengthError is True. When this parameter is configured as 0, it mean allowing messages with any Payload Length pass the Icom receive message configuration.

This container contains the configuration parameters for the wakeup causes for matching signals. It has to be configured as often as a signal is defined as wakeup cause. If at least one Signal conditions defined in a CanIcomRxMessageSignalConfig evaluates to true or if no CanIcomRxMessageSignalConfig are defined, the whole wakeup condition is considered to be true. All instances of this container refer to the same frame/pdu (see CanIcomMessageId).

This parameter shall be used to mask a signal in the payload of a CAN message. The mask is binary AND with the signal payload. The result will be used in combination of the operations defined in CanIcomSignalOperation with the CanIcomSignalValue.
This parameter defines the operation, which shall be used to verify the signal value creates a wakeup condition.

P.L-1: AND: The received signal value masked by CanIcomSignalMask has at least one bit set in common with CanIcomSignalValue (binary AND). EQUAL: The received signal value masked by CanIcomSignalMask is equal to CanIcomSignalValue. GREATER: The received signal value masked by CanIcomSignalMask is strictly greater than CanIcomSignalValue. Values are interpreted as unsigned integers. SMALLER: The received signal value masked by CanIcomSignalMask is strictly smaller than CanIcomSignalValue. Values are interpreted as unsigned integers. XOR: The received signal value masked by CanIcomSignalMask then XORed to CanIcomSignalValue is not null.

DESC.L-2: This parameter shall be used to define a signal value which shall be compared (CanIcomSignalOperation) with the masked CanIcomSignalMask value of the received signal (CanIcomSignalRef).

This parameter defines a reference to the signal which shall be checked additional to the message id (CanIcomMessageId). This reference is used for documentation to define which ComSignal originates this filter setting. All signals being referred by this reference shall point to the same PDU.

P.L-1: Implementation Type: Reference to ComSignal.

DESC.L-2: Container for the references to DemEventParameter elements which shall be invoked using the API Dem_ReportErrorStatus API in case the corresponding error occurs. The EventId is taken from the referenced DemEventParameter's DemEventId value. The standardized errors are provided in the container and can be extended by vendor specific error references.
Reference to configured DEM event to report "Error Register Read Verify".
Reference to configured DEM event to report "Error Register Write Verify".
Reference to configured DEM event to report "Timeout Failure".
This parameter is for functional safety, user shall refer Safety Application Note for description or leave it with default value. Reference to configured DEM event to report "Unintended Interrupt".
This parameter shall not be configured.
This container contains the parameters related each CAN Driver Unit.
This parameter enables/disables the CAN_E_TRANSITION DET check in Can_Init API.

P.L-1:
true: Enables the CAN_E_TRANSITION DET check in Can_Init API. false: Disables the CAN_E_TRANSITION DET check in Can_Init API.
When the CAN Driver is re-initialized , this parameter is set as false to suppress the check for CAN_E_TRANSITION DET error. This parameter has no impact when DET is disabled.

DESC.L-2: Switch the Can_ChangeBaudrate API ON or OFF.

P.L-1: true: Switch Can_ChangeBaudrate API to ON. false: Switch Can_ChangeBaudrate API to OFF.

DESC.L-2: Specify whether the CAN driver CPU load can be reduced by disabling the enter/exit critical section functionality.

P.L-1: true: Enable the critical section functionality for the restricted area. false: Disable the critical section functionality for the restricted area.

DESC.L-2: Switch the Development Error Detection and Notification ON or OFF.

P.L-1: true: Switch Error Detection and Notification to ON. false: Switch Error Detection and Notification to OFF.

DESC.L-2: This parameter contains the supported device name to identify the device specific C header file through Translation XML File.

P.L-1: RCar_V3Hv2: This value should be child tag of TRANSLATION-FILE-PATH and DEVICE-FILE-PATH tag in Translation XML File.

DESC.L-2: This parameter contains version of device.

P.L-1: RCar-V3Hv2: V3H_WS2_0: Working Sample Version 2.0

DESC.L-2: Specify whether the Extended CanId shall be supported .

P.L-1: true: Switch Extended CanId support to ON. false: Switch Extended CanId support to OFF.

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies the InstanceId of this module instance. If only one instance is present it shall have the Id 0. This parameter is not used for implementation, since hardware does not support this functionality.

This parameter is for functional safety, user shall refer Safety Application Note for description or leave it with default value. This parameter is used to select RFSO channel for Unintended Interrupt Check safety mechanism.

P.L-1: RFSO_DISABLE: Disable using RFSO. RFSO_0: Channel 0. RFSO_1: Channel 1. RFSO_2: Channel 2. RFSO_3: Channel 3. RFSO_4: Channel 4. RFSO_5: Channel 5. RFSO_6: Channel 6. RFSO_7: Channel 7. RFSO_8: Channel 8. RFSO_9: Channel 9. RFSO_10: Channel 10.

DESC.L-2: This parameter defines the existence and the name of a Callout function that is called after a successful CAN message reception.

P.L-1: Successful reception of a received CAN Rx L-PDU. If this parameter is omitted no Callout shall take place.

DESC.L-2: Specify whether Callout function shall be supported.

P.L-1: true: Switch Callout function support to ON. false: Switch Callout function support to OFF.

DESC.L-2: This parameter describes the period for cyclic call to Can_MainFunction_Busoff. Unit is seconds.
This parameter describes the period for cyclic call to Can_MainFunction_Mode. Unit is seconds.

This parameter describes the period for cyclic call to Can_MainFunction_Wakeup. Unit is seconds. This parameters is not used for implementation since CAN HW doesn't support wakeup detection over CAN bus.
This parameter shall be configured as RFSO_DISABLE
Specify whether Multiplexed transmission shall be supported. This parameter is not used for implementation.

P.L-1: CAN driver provides hardware Multiplexed Transmission mechanism by configured TRANSMIT CanHardwareObject in TRANSMIT_RECEIVE_FIFO_MODE or TRANSMIT_QUEUE_MODE, which send L-PDUs in order of L-PDU priority to avoid transmit priority inversion.

DESC.L-2: Selects support of Pretended Network features in Can driver.

P.L-1: true: Enable support of Pretended Network features. false: Disable support of Pretended Network features.

DESC.L-2: Switch the CAN_RAMTest API ON or OFF.

P.L-1: true: Switch CAN_RAMTest API to ON. false: Switch CAN_RAMTest API to OFF.

DESC.L-2: This parameter enables selection and support of RV_ENABLE or RV_DISABLE register read-verify functionality of CAN registers.

P.L-1: RV_ENABLE: Enables read-verify functionality for CAN registers. RV_DISABLE: Disables read-verify functionality for CAN registers.

DESC.L-2: This parameter is used to select RFSO channel for Register Read Verify functionality.

P.L-1: RFSO_DISABLE: Disable using RFSO.

DESC.L-2: The support of the Can_SetBaudrate API is optional.

P.L-1: If this parameter is set to true the Can_SetBaudrate API shall be supported. Otherwise the API is not supported.

DESC.L-2: This paramter specifies the maximum time for blocking function until a Timeout is detected. Unit is seconds.

This parameter is for functional safety, user shall refer Safety Application Note for description or leave it with default value. This parameter is used to enable/disable safety mechanism Unintended Interrupt Check for CAN.

P.L-1: true: Switch Unintended Interrupt Check to ON. false: Switch Unintended Interrupt Check to OFF.

DESC.L-2: This parameter shall be configured false.
Specify whether AUTOSAR Version Check for inter-module dependencies shall be supported.

P.L-1: true: Switch AUTOSAR Version Check for inter-module dependencies to ON. false: Switch AUTOSAR Version Check for inter-module dependencies to OFF.

DESC.L-2: Switch the Can_GetVersionInfo API ON or OFF.

P.L-1: true: Switch Can_GetVersionInfo API to ON. false: Switch Can_GetVersionInfo API to OFF.

DESC.L-2: This parameter enables selection and support of WV_INIT_ONLY, WV_INIT_RUNTIME or WV_DISABLE register write-verify functionality of CAN registers.

P.L-1: WV_INIT_ONLY: Enables write-verify functionality on static registers. WV_INIT_RUNTIME: Enables write-verify functionality on static and dynamic registers. WV_DISABLE: Disables the register write-verify functionality for CAN registers.

DESC.L-2: This parameter is used to select RFSO channel for Register Write Verify functionality.

P.L-1: RFSO_DISABLE: Disable using RFSO.

DESC.L-2: This parameter contains a reference to the OS counter, which is used by the CAN driver.

P.L-1: Implementation Type: reference to OsCounter.

DESC.L-2: The parameter refers to CanIfSupportTTCAN parameter in the CAN Interface Module configuration. This parameter is not used for implementation, since hardware does not support TTCAN functionality.

P.L-1: The CanIfSupportTTCAN parameter defines whether TTCAN is supported.

DESC.L-2: This container contains the read and write parameters related to CAN general.

This parameter describes the period for cyclic call to Can_MainFunction_Read or Can_MainFunction_Write depending on the referring item. Unit is seconds. Different poll-cycles will be configurable if more than one CanMainFunctionPeriod is configured. In this case multiple Can_MainFunction_Read() or Can_MainFunction_Write() will be provided by the CAN Driver module. This parameter is not used for implementation.

This parameter describes the period for cyclic call to Can_MainFunction_Read. Unit is seconds. Different poll-cycles will be configurable if more than one CanMainFunctionReadPeriod is configured. In this case multiple Can_MainFunction_Read() will be provided by the CAN Driver module.

This parameter describes the period for cyclic call to Can_MainFunction_Write. Unit is seconds. Different poll-cycles will be configurable if more than one CanMainFunctionWritePeriod is configured. In this case multiple Can_MainFunction_Write() will be provided by the CAN Driver module.
This container contains the general configuration parameters of the ICOM Configuration.
This parameter defines the existence and the name of a Callout function that is called if Payload Length Error occurs when CAN Pretended Networking is activation.

P.L-1: Payload Length Error occurs when CAN Pretended Networking is activation. If this parameter is omitted no Callout shall take place.

DESC.L-2: Defines the level of Pretended Networking. This parameter is reserved for future implementations (Pretended Networking level 2).
Defines the variant, which is supported by this CanController.
This container contains the parameters related to Global configuration register(RSCFDnGCFG) for RS-CANFD Driver Unit.
This parameter is used to select a clock source of the CAN clock (fCAN). This parameter represents the DCS bit in RSCFDnGCFG Global Configuration Register.

P.L-1: true: External clock CAN_CLK is used as the clock source of the CAN clock (fCAN). false: CANFD clock is used as the clock source of the CAN clock(fCAN). The configured value of parameter CanControllerClock is considered as clock source (fCAN).

DESC.L-2: This parameter represents the CAN_CLK clock which is set in the MCU driver configuration. This clock is considered only when the parameter CanClockSourceSelect(i.e. DCS bit) is configured as TRUE.
Specify whether Data Length Check for the Receive Rule shall be supported. This parameter represents the DCE bit in RSCFDnGCFG Global Configuration Register.

P.L-1: true: Switch Data Length Check for the Receive Rule support to ON. false: Switch Data Length Check for the Receive Rule support to OFF.

DESC.L-2: Specifies if the flexible data rate feature shall be supported or not by the CANFD. This parameter represents the RCMC bit in RSCANFDnCFDGRMCFG Global Interface Mode Register.

P.L-1: true: FD support will be ON. false: FD support will be OFF.

DESC.L-2: This parameter specifies clock source division value of the interval timer for FIFO buffers. This parameter represents the ITRCP[15:0] bits in RSCFDnGCFG Global Configuration Register. pclk clock is divided by the configured value of this parameter.
Specify whether the mirror function shall be supported. This parameter represents the MME bit in RSCFDnGCFG Global Configuration Register.

P.L-1: true: Switch Mirror Function support to ON. false: Switch Mirror Function support to OFF.

DESC.L-2: This parameter is used to divide the clock source (selected by the parameters CanTimestampClockSourceSelect(TSS) and CanTimestampSourceSelect(TSBTCS[2:0])). This parameter represents the TSP[3:0] bits in RSCFDnGCFG Global Configuration Register.

P.L-1: DIVIDED_BY_1: Divided by 1. DIVIDED_BY_2: Divided by 2. DIVIDED_BY_4: Divided by 4. DIVIDED_BY_8: Divided by 8. DIVIDED_BY_16: Divided by 16. DIVIDED_BY_32: Divided by 32. DIVIDED_BY_64: Divided by 64. DIVIDED_BY_128: Divided by 128. DIVIDED_BY_256: Divided by 256. DIVIDED_BY_512: Divided by 512. DIVIDED_BY_1024: Divided by 1024. DIVIDED_BY_2048: Divided by 2048. DIVIDED_BY_4096: Divided by 4096. DIVIDED_BY_8192: Divided by 8192. DIVIDED_BY_16384: Divided by 16384. DIVIDED_BY_32768: Divided by 32768.

DESC.L-2: This parameter is used to select a channel bit time clock as the clock source for the timestamp counter. This parameter represents the TSBTCS[2:0] bits in RSCFDnGCFG Global Configuration Register. This parameter is applicable only when the parameter CanTimestampSourceSelect is configured as TRUE (i.e. TSSS bit is 1).

P.L-1: CHANNEL0_BIT_TIMECLK: Channel 0 bit time clock is selected. CHANNEL1_BIT_TIMECLK: Channel 1 bit time clock is selected. CHANNEL2_BIT_TIMECLK: Channel 2 bit time clock is selected.

DESC.L-2: This parameter is used to select a clock source for the timestamp counter. This parameter represents the TSSS bit in RSCFDnGCFG Global Configuration Register.

P.L-1: true: Timestamp Clock Source is Bit time clock selected by the parameter CanTimestampClockSourceSelect. false: Timestamp Clock Source is pclk/2.

DESC.L-2: This parameter is used to select the Transmit Priority in Global Configuration Register(RSCFDnGCFG). This parameter represents the TPRI bit in RSCFDnGCFG Global Configuration Register.

P.L-1: true: Transmit buffer number priority is selected and the lowest transmit buffer number of those has the highest priority. false: ID priority is selected and the transmit priority complies with the CAN bus arbitration rule (ISO11898-1 specifications).

DESC.L-2: Specify whether storing the Timestamp of the transmission completed message into Transmit History Buffer shall be supported. Time stamp on completion of a message transmission in only available in classical CAN mode. This parameter represents the TMTSCE bit in RSCFDnGCFG Global Configuration Register.

P.L-1: true: Switch Transmit Timestamp to ON. false: Switch Transmit Timestamp to OFF.

DESC.L-2: This parameter represents the CANFD clock which is set in the MCU driver configuration. This clock is considered only when the parameter CanClockSourceSelect(i.e. DCS bit) is configured as FALSE.

P.L-1: Implementation Type: reference to McuCanPclk.

DESC.L-2: This parameter represents the S3D2 clock which is set in the MCU driver configuration.

P.L-1: Implementation Type: reference to McuCanPclk.
